dc_description_s: The Five-Year Transportation Program (5YTP) is an annual document listing road and bridge projects planned for the next five years. A snapshot of 5YTP projects is produced annually and presented for approval to the State Transportation Commission. The 5YTP snapshot is later archived and the document is posted on MDOTs Web site. A Web-based interactive state map is available which plots individual projects for the public to easily view. Please see theMDOT Metadata Formfor additional information or visit the5YTP Website.Update Cycle:The Five Year Transportation Program (5YTP) layer was last updated in January 2016 and is updated on an annual basis.;Data Quality:The GIS layer is generated from MDOTs MAP database 5YTP archive snapshot.;Coverage:This layer covers all projects in the current 5YTP snapshot.;Contact:Eric Mullen,mullene@michigan.gov
